scripts.build: npm test && npm run build64 && npm run build32
scripts.build64: npm run build:macos && npm run build:linux && npm run build:windows64
scripts.build32: npm run build:linux32 && npm run build:windows

releases.name: v3.0.3
releases.body: - Added Windows 32bit version build fixing issue #85

releases.name: v3.0.0
releases.body:
- Auto update
- Structure
- AppImage build
- Mac DMG build
- New icon

- Fixed incorrect scrolling issues #18 #36 - Thanks @VoOoLoX 
- UI tweaks to dark mode (66529ad and 96dbacd)
- Awesome new scroll by post feature #46 - Thanks @VoOoLoX 
- Updated dependencies
- Now with JavaScript Standard Style

I appreciate every commit from the all the amazing contributors, thanks!

- Update notifications for new releases added #14 
- Fixed drag issue #36 #42 
- Design tweaks for better performance and more native field
- New builds #37
- New, more user friendly website at https://terkelg.github.io/ramme/ #35 #15 

I think most of the known bugs are fixed by now, and we are ready to look at new features.

Thanks @anatolinicolae @seanr707 @vintagesucks @stephenkingsley @brejoc and @seven11nash

- Added tray icon to Windows and Linux #21
- Fixed #19 where process continues to run on Windows.
- Fixed Dark Mode toggle #25 #27 

Thanks to the contributors, @neighborhood999 and @vintagesucks.

- Dark mode! (High-five [@ninjaprawn](https://github.com/ninjaprawn))
- Shortcuts
- Switched from HTTP to HTTPS
- Removed “Open in App”
- Design tweaks for Windows and Linux 

Thanks to the folks who contributed. 
_I still have a lot to learn when it comes to managing open-source projects._
First version of Ramme - The unofficial Instagram desktop client, build with Electron.
